United Lacrosse League (ULL) Summer 2020 Waivers


WAIVER & RELEASE OF LIABILITY:

I am fully aware of and appreciate the risks, including the risk of catastrophic injury, paralysis and even death, as well as other damages and losses, associated with participation in lacrosse programming and / or a lacrosse event. I further agree, on behalf of myself, my heirs, and personal representatives, that United Sport Holdings, Inc., along with the coaches, volunteers, employees, agents, officers and directors of these organizations, shall not be liable for any injury, loss of life or other loss or damage occurring as a result of my participation in lacrosse programming and / or a lacrosse event, or as a result of equipment that may have been provided to me for these activities. 

MEDICAL ATTENTION:

I hereby give my consent to United Sport Holdings, Inc. to provide, through a medical staff of its choice, customary medical/athletic training attention, transportation and/ or emergency medical services as warranted in the course of my participation in United Sport Holdings, Inc. programming or events. 

READINESS TO COMPETE:

The above named participant is in good health and proper physical condition to participate in United Sport Holdings, Inc., programming and / or events. 

PHOTO WAIVER & RELEASE AGREEMENT:

I hereby give my consent to United Sport Holdings, Inc., and its partners and sponsors to use photos/videos taken of my son/daughter while attending United Sport Holdings, Inc., programming or events on United Sport Holdings, Inc. marketing materials, both online and in print. 

REFUND AGREEMENT:

I understand that due to the nature and expense of pre-planned events, tournaments, camps, clinics, workshops, and select teams, United Sport Holdings, Inc., has a policy of no refunds. 

MEDICAL COVERAGE:

I confirm my participant is covered by our own Medical Insurance

CANCELLATION:

I understand that in the event of a program cancellation due to events outside the control of United Sport Holdings, Inc., (e.g., weather), United Sport Holdings, Inc. will do its best to reschedule the event within a reasonable timeframe, and that I am not entitled to a refund merely because of a change in time or date. 


WAIVER/RELEASE FOR COMMUNICABLE DISEASES INCLUDING COVID-19 ASSUMPTION OF RISK / WAIVER OF

LIABILITY / INDEMNIFICATION AGREEMENT

 

To meet the standards of local government and health authorities, all participants (families) must complete the following Covid-19 Screening and waiver in order to participate in United Sport Holdings practices/camps/games. This from must be completed to participate. Failure to do so will unfortunately result in you being turned away. Thank you in advance for your understanding and attention to this matter.

 

In consideration of being allowed to participate on behalf of United Sport Holdings Inc. athletic program and related events and activities, the undersigned acknowledges, appreciates, and agrees that: 1. Participation includes possible exposure to and illness from infectious diseases including but not limited to MRSA, influenza, and COVID-19. While particular rules and personal discipline may reduce this risk, the risk of serious illness and death does exist; and, 2. I KNOWINGLY AND FREELY ASSUME ALL SUCH RISKS, both known and unknown, EVEN IF ARISING FROM THE NEGLIGENCE OF THE RELEASEES or others, and assume full responsibility for my participation; and, 3. I willingly agree to comply with the stated and customary terms and conditions for participation as regards protection against infectious diseases. If, however, I observe and any unusual or significant hazard during my presence or participation, I will remove myself from participation and bring such to the attention of the nearest official immediately; and, 4. I, for myself and on behalf of my heirs, assigns, personal representatives and next of kin, HEREBY RELEASE AND HOLD HARMLESS United Sport Holdings Inc. their officers, officials, agents, and/or employees, other participants, sponsoring agencies, sponsors, advertisers, and if applicable, owners and lessors of premises used to conduct the event, WITH RESPECT TO ANY AND ALL ILLNESS, DISABILITY, DEATH, or loss or damage to person or property, WHETHER ARISING FROM THE NEGLIGENCE OF RELEASEES OR OTHERWISE, to the fullest extent permitted by law. I HAVE READ THIS RELEASE OF LIABILITY AND ASSUMPTION OF RISK AGREEMENT, FULLY UNDERSTAND ITS TERMS, UNDERSTAND THAT I HAVE GIVEN UP SUBSTANTIAL RIGHTS BY SIGNING IT, AND SIGN IF FREELY AND VOLUNTARILY WITHOUT ANY INDUCEMENT.

 

FOR PARTICIPANTS OF MINORITY AGE (UNDER AGE 18 AT THE TIME OF REGISTRATION)

This is to certify that I, as parent/guardian, with legal responsibility for this participant, have read and explained the provisions in this waiver/release to my child/ward including the risks of presence and participation and his/her personal responsibilities for adhering to the rules and regulations for protection against communicable diseases. Furthermore, my child/ward understands and accepts these risks and responsibilities. I for myself, my spouse, and child/ward do consent and agree to his/her release provided above for all the Releasees and myself, my spouse, and child/ward do release and agree to indemnify and hold harmless the Releasees for any and all liabilities incident to my minor child’s/ward’s presence or participation in these activities as provided above, EVEN IF ARISING FROM THEIR NEGLIGENCE, to the fullest extent provided by law.

 

COVID-19 ACTIVE SCREENING QUESTIONNAIRE

 

This will be updated as the Provincial and Regional government and health agencies information on COVID-19 continues to change. Your health and well-being are of the upmost importance and we are taking measures to keep the facilities a safe environment for participants as well as coaching staff, family members and the public. Therefore, anyone

participating at the event will be screened and part of our screening process will asking the following questions.

 

Within the last 14 days, you attest that the participant:

1.    Has not experienced a new cough that you cannot attribute to another health condition

2.    Has not experienced new shortness of breath that you cannot attribute to another health condition

3.    Has not experienced a new sore throat that you cannot attribute to another health condition

4.    Has not experienced new muscle aches that you cannot attribute to another health condition or a specific activity such as physical exercise

5.    Has not had a temperature at or above 100.5 degrees Fahrenheit or has the sense of having a fever

6.    Has no had close contact, without the use of appropriate PPE, with someone who is currently sick with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 (Note: Close contact is defined as within 6 feet for more than 10 consecutive minutes)


If the athlete or family member answers yes to any of the questions above, they will not be allowed into the facility unless they can provide confirmed negative test results for Covid-19 within the past two (2) weeks.

 

I recognize the above Waiver of Liability & Indemnification Agreement as well as attest the my representations within the Covid-19 Screening Questionnaire is true to the best of my knowledge.
